Preconditions:
- The input array `arr` must not be null.
- The input array `arr` must have at least one element.
- The input array `arr` must contain only non-negative integers.
- The input integer `start` must be a valid index within the array `arr`.

Postconditions:
- The method returns a boolean value indicating whether it is possible to reach any index with value 0.
- If it is possible to reach any index with value 0, the method returns true.
- If it is not possible to reach any index with value 0, the method returns false.